1
00:00:13,947 --> 00:00:17,008
<i>- See you Tuesday.
- How about right now?</i>

2
00:00:17,084 --> 00:00:19,417
<i>What? What?</i>

3
00:00:21,421 --> 00:00:22,499
<i>You wanna throw in the towel?</i>

4
00:00:22,523 --> 00:00:24,083
<i>No, I don't wanna
throw in the... towel!</i>

5
00:00:24,124 --> 00:00:25,990
<i>I thought that's what you said!</i>

6
00:00:26,059 --> 00:00:27,891
<i>I'm not upset about anything!</i>

7
00:00:30,397 --> 00:00:32,389
<i>Where the... are we going?</i>

8
00:00:32,799 --> 00:00:33,843
What are you doing down here?

9
00:00:33,867 --> 00:00:36,632
I thought you usually
had lunch with Coma Guy.

10
00:00:36,703 --> 00:00:39,502
This is Vegetative State
Guy. Better company.

11
00:00:40,073 --> 00:00:42,042
Hey, hey, tell him
about those Sherpas

12
00:00:42,109 --> 00:00:44,374
you dropped acid with in
Saint Patrick's Cathedral.

13
00:00:44,444 --> 00:00:48,211
You stole my prescription
pad and you forged my name.

14
00:00:50,984 --> 00:00:52,782
What did you
tell the cop? I lied.

15
00:00:52,853 --> 00:00:54,333
They'd have put you
away for 10 years,

16
00:00:54,388 --> 00:00:56,653
after they took your
license to practice medicine.

17
00:00:56,723 --> 00:00:57,986
So, everything's good, then.

18
00:00:58,058 --> 00:01:00,084
I lied. To the cops.

19
00:01:00,160 --> 00:01:01,856
There is no case
unless they can prove

20
00:01:01,929 --> 00:01:04,763
that either I got the drugs
illegally or I sold them illegally.

21
00:01:04,831 --> 00:01:07,110
I didn't do the second, you
lied about the first. Game over.

22
00:01:07,134 --> 00:01:08,727
Yeah, Tritter's just playing.

23
00:01:08,802 --> 00:01:11,465
He's gonna see how clever
you are and then just walk away.

24
00:01:11,538 --> 00:01:13,182
The important thing is
that you keep prescribing

25
00:01:13,206 --> 00:01:15,971
the same amount of drugs
to me or it'll look suspicious.

26
00:01:16,043 --> 00:01:17,323
Here's another
way to look at it,

27
00:01:17,377 --> 00:01:19,312
having forced me
to lie to the police,

28
00:01:19,379 --> 00:01:22,679
your first concern is
securing your drug connection.

29
00:01:28,288 --> 00:01:30,280
Joining my father for lunch?

30
00:01:30,757 --> 00:01:32,282
I should have called
ahead for a table.

31
00:01:32,359 --> 00:01:33,486
Dr. House was just...

32
00:01:33,560 --> 00:01:35,222
Enjoying a Reuben.

33
00:01:35,662 --> 00:01:36,755
It's okay.

34
00:01:37,297 --> 00:01:40,961
After 10 years, anything that'll
get doctors in the same room as...

35
00:01:42,436 --> 00:01:44,405
What are you doing? Nothing.

36
00:01:44,471 --> 00:01:46,235
What are you doing?

37
00:01:48,575 --> 00:01:49,838
Chips?

38
00:01:52,980 --> 00:01:55,711
Wanna see something really cool?

39
00:02:02,356 --> 00:02:04,723
I saw you leaving last Tuesday.

40
00:02:05,292 --> 00:02:07,523
You practically tripped over
two guys on your way out,

41
00:02:07,594 --> 00:02:09,529
but you had no
problem opening doors.

42
00:02:09,596 --> 00:02:11,292
It's called akinetopsia.

43
00:02:11,798 --> 00:02:13,596
You can't see things
when they move.

44
00:02:13,667 --> 00:02:17,104
Now, since you haven't been hit by
a bus, I assume that it's intermittent.

45
00:02:17,170 --> 00:02:18,581
It's probably
accompanied by seizures,

46
00:02:18,605 --> 00:02:22,064
which made me think that I
could set one off by flashing the...

47
00:02:27,814 --> 00:02:30,215
God, I love this family.

48
00:03:09,623 --> 00:03:11,353
I can see fine now.

49
00:03:12,759 --> 00:03:16,127
I've had seizures before.
Most of the time they're small.

50
00:03:16,196 --> 00:03:19,758
Doctors ran me through all
the tests. Couldn't find anything.

51
00:03:19,833 --> 00:03:22,098
Any history of
epilepsy in your family?

52
00:03:22,169 --> 00:03:24,161
The only things I know
that run in my family are

53
00:03:24,237 --> 00:03:27,935
a lot of chutzpah and the
ability to sleep for 10 years.

54
00:03:28,408 --> 00:03:29,842
Although I'm not
really an expert.

55
00:03:29,910 --> 00:03:32,021
Dad never really liked my
mother's side of the family,

56
00:03:32,045 --> 00:03:36,141
and after she died and he came
here I was raised by a guardian.

57
00:03:37,117 --> 00:03:39,348
I wouldn't even know how
to get in touch with them.

58
00:03:39,419 --> 00:03:41,030
How about your father's
side of the family?

59
00:03:41,054 --> 00:03:42,454
Any relatives we
could speak with?

60
00:03:42,522 --> 00:03:44,081
My father was an only child.

61
00:03:44,157 --> 00:03:45,523
And my grandparents are dead.

62
00:03:45,592 --> 00:03:46,787
Well, who did you put down

63
00:03:46,860 --> 00:03:49,659
as the person the hospital
should contact in an emergency?

64
00:03:49,730 --> 00:03:50,789
I left it blank.

65
00:03:50,864 --> 00:03:52,526
There's gotta be
someone, a friend...

66
00:03:52,599 --> 00:03:53,794
I have plenty of friends.

67
00:03:53,867 --> 00:03:56,393
Just no one that
would care if I was here.

68
00:03:59,139 --> 00:04:01,665
Say, do you mind
passing me my backpack?

69
00:04:16,590 --> 00:04:18,491
Hair of the dog.

70
00:04:21,595 --> 00:04:23,791
- Could be infection.
- Or a brain tumor.

71
00:04:23,864 --> 00:04:24,991
Says he had a CT.

72
00:04:25,065 --> 00:04:27,159
What's wrong with the
simplest explanation? Trauma?

73
00:04:27,234 --> 00:04:28,497
He didn't report any injuries.

74
00:04:28,568 --> 00:04:30,628
He didn't report being
an alcoholic, either.

75
00:04:30,704 --> 00:04:33,299
Drinking equals falling
down equals trauma equals...

76
00:04:33,373 --> 00:04:34,466
Maybe it's inherited.

77
00:04:34,541 --> 00:04:38,069
How would you jump to
genetics from his EEG?

78
00:04:38,512 --> 00:04:40,879
All you've got are some
vaguely epileptiform waves.

79
00:04:40,947 --> 00:04:44,247
It's not his EEG.
It's his father's.

80
00:04:44,317 --> 00:04:47,287
When it comes to cortical
seizures, like father, like son.

81
00:04:47,354 --> 00:04:48,913
Small seizures aren't unheard of

82
00:04:48,989 --> 00:04:50,389
in a patient in a
vegetative state.

83
00:04:50,457 --> 00:04:52,050
Similarities are
interesting, though.

84
00:04:52,125 --> 00:04:53,718
What caused the
vegetative state?

85
00:04:53,794 --> 00:04:55,524
His house burned down.

86
00:04:55,829 --> 00:04:57,195
Went back in to get his wife,

87
00:04:57,264 --> 00:04:58,857
firefighters found
him unconscious

88
00:04:58,932 --> 00:05:00,992
three feet from the
bedroom, asphyxiated.

89
00:05:01,067 --> 00:05:02,899
Not an inherited condition.

90
00:05:02,969 --> 00:05:06,701
Test his DNA. Start with
adrenomyeloneuropathy.

91
00:05:07,307 --> 00:05:09,003
Check out the home.

92
00:05:15,582 --> 00:05:17,016
He has a single bed.

93
00:05:17,083 --> 00:05:18,381
They still make single beds?

94
00:05:18,451 --> 00:05:20,352
It could mean he
just doesn't have sex,

95
00:05:20,420 --> 00:05:22,821
though there were
condoms in the apartment.

96
00:05:23,156 --> 00:05:25,921
House asked you to check
out the home for toxins.

97
00:05:25,992 --> 00:05:28,393
No mold, no leaks, no pets.

98
00:05:28,461 --> 00:05:30,623
MRI and LP are
both inconclusive.

99
00:05:30,697 --> 00:05:32,642
Infection's still possible,
tumor's less likely, but...

100
00:05:32,666 --> 00:05:34,692
DNA? The
adrenomyeloneuropathy test

101
00:05:34,768 --> 00:05:35,768
was negative.

102
00:05:35,836 --> 00:05:36,997
DNA test again.

103
00:05:37,070 --> 00:05:39,266
Try Unverricht-Lundborg
and late-onset Lafora's.

104
00:05:39,339 --> 00:05:40,739
Genetic tests take forever.

105
00:05:40,807 --> 00:05:43,967
You can't just keep testing for every
inherited condition you think it might be.

106
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:47,037
Well, not me. I'll be leaving
early. But you guys can.

107
00:05:51,051 --> 00:05:54,579
You said no one's been sick but
what about delivery people, repair guy?

108
00:05:54,654 --> 00:05:57,214
I wouldn't know.
I work from home.

109
00:05:57,691 --> 00:05:59,489
Haven't been to the
office in over a month.

110
00:05:59,559 --> 00:06:00,720
Visitors?

111
00:06:00,794 --> 00:06:02,023
Haven't had any.

112
00:06:02,095 --> 00:06:03,961
The only person I've
seen in the last week

113
00:06:04,030 --> 00:06:07,398
was the pizza delivery guy
and he looked pretty healthy.

114
00:06:07,834 --> 00:06:10,565
There's gotta be
someone you're close to.

115
00:06:11,071 --> 00:06:14,633
Actually, the person I
see most often is my father.

116
00:06:15,609 --> 00:06:18,704
He's asleep so he can't stop me.

117
00:06:23,250 --> 00:06:24,343
What is it?

118
00:06:24,417 --> 00:06:26,852
I'm just feeling
a little nauseous.

119
00:06:30,257 --> 00:06:31,816
I think his liver's failing.

120
00:06:31,892 --> 00:06:34,760
God. Does that mean that I'm...

121
00:06:39,866 --> 00:06:40,959
We need a central line kit,

122
00:06:41,034 --> 00:06:44,198
two units of packed red
blood cells type O Negative.

123
00:06:45,705 --> 00:06:47,697
He's unconscious and
heading for a coma.

124
00:06:47,774 --> 00:06:49,709
He's at a four on
the RLAS scale.

125
00:06:51,177 --> 00:06:53,146
Stop all treatment.

126
00:06:53,446 --> 00:06:55,711
You think this is a
reaction to our meds?

127
00:06:55,782 --> 00:06:57,978
Well, they're
obviously not helping.

128
00:06:58,318 --> 00:06:59,662
Given the fact that
he's an alcoholic,

129
00:06:59,686 --> 00:07:02,031
there's a good chance his liver
wasn't so hot when he came in.

130
00:07:02,055 --> 00:07:04,415
Anti-seizure drugs could have
just pushed him over the edge.

131
00:07:04,457 --> 00:07:07,052
We take him off those
meds, what do we put him on?

132
00:07:07,127 --> 00:07:08,220
I was hoping you'd know.

133
00:07:08,361 --> 00:07:11,593
It may be academic, I
just started him on dialysis.

134
00:07:11,665 --> 00:07:15,500
Kidney and liver failure. Not too
many people come back from that.

135
00:07:15,568 --> 00:07:17,764
Trauma's out of the picture.
Could still be infection.

136
00:07:17,837 --> 00:07:20,068
Or neurological... Or genetic.

137
00:07:20,807 --> 00:07:23,402
We need a better history.

138
00:07:24,244 --> 00:07:27,510
Did you miss the part where
the patient lost consciousness?

139
00:07:29,015 --> 00:07:30,950
L-dopa?

140
00:07:31,751 --> 00:07:34,448
You're not waking Kyle.
You're waking his father.

141
00:07:34,521 --> 00:07:36,547
I commend your
observational skills.

142
00:07:36,623 --> 00:07:37,750
You have no reason to think

143
00:07:37,824 --> 00:07:40,123
any amount of drugs will
wake a man from a coma.

144
00:07:40,193 --> 00:07:42,025
Vegetative state. Much easier.

145
00:07:42,095 --> 00:07:44,963
This guy's no Terry Schiavo, his
brain's all there, he moves around,

146
00:07:45,031 --> 00:07:46,727
his muscles have
barely atrophied.

147
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:49,099
He's just waiting
for a fairy-tale kiss.

148
00:07:49,169 --> 00:07:51,729
After I do that, I'll
stick a needle in him.

149
00:07:53,907 --> 00:07:56,741
The amount of amphetamines
alone would be dangerous,

150
00:07:56,810 --> 00:07:59,006
besides whatever the
hell else you've got in there.

151
00:07:59,079 --> 00:08:01,173
There are reports
out of South Africa

152
00:08:01,247 --> 00:08:05,548
about a pill that would temporarily
revive someone in a vegetative state.

153
00:08:05,618 --> 00:08:08,213
You've all seen
<i>Awakenings,</i> made me cry.

154
00:08:08,855 --> 00:08:10,050
I wanna cry.

155
00:08:10,724 --> 00:08:12,215
Put the syringe down.

156
00:08:14,260 --> 00:08:16,593
I can outdraw you,
mysterious stranger.

157
00:08:16,663 --> 00:08:18,791
We don't experiment
on helpless patients.

158
00:08:18,865 --> 00:08:21,164
Be reasonable. There's
no way this is gonna work.

159
00:08:21,234 --> 00:08:23,931
Even if you woke him, it
would only be for a few hours.

160
00:08:24,004 --> 00:08:25,836
A day, two at the most.

161
00:08:25,905 --> 00:08:27,305
You're risking his life.

162
00:08:27,374 --> 00:08:30,173
I'm risking getting sued,
that's the only objection here.

163
00:08:30,243 --> 00:08:32,712
You'll be torturing
him and his family.

164
00:08:33,279 --> 00:08:36,215
Well, good news for Legal, the
only family he's got is upstairs dying.

165
00:08:36,282 --> 00:08:37,614
Hey!

166
00:08:45,625 --> 00:08:48,424
I want this patient monitored
for the next 24 hours.

167
00:08:48,495 --> 00:08:50,225
I want someone
with him at all times

168
00:08:50,296 --> 00:08:51,730
to make sure
you didn't kill him.

169
00:08:51,798 --> 00:08:54,029
I want your ass in my office.

170
00:08:56,102 --> 00:08:58,571
God, I'm starving.

171
00:09:01,574 --> 00:09:04,567
I could really go for a steak.

172
00:09:10,250 --> 00:09:13,186
Do you know your name?
Do you know where you are?

173
00:09:14,287 --> 00:09:17,314
Gabriel Wozniak. I don't
know the name of this hospital.

174
00:09:17,390 --> 00:09:19,586
How much are three and five?

175
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:21,521
Eight.

176
00:09:21,694 --> 00:09:25,722
Also known as half of 16, a
quarter of 32, two to the third power.

177
00:09:27,033 --> 00:09:28,592
Coolest thing ever.

178
00:09:28,668 --> 00:09:30,967
Any history of
seizure in your family?

179
00:09:31,037 --> 00:09:32,801
No. Liver disease?

180
00:09:32,872 --> 00:09:33,896
No.

181
00:09:33,973 --> 00:09:36,204
How long have I been here?

182
00:09:36,876 --> 00:09:39,038
I got the feeling it's
been a long time.

183
00:09:39,112 --> 00:09:40,136
Interesting.

184
00:09:40,213 --> 00:09:42,546
Your internal
clock kept ticking.

185
00:09:42,849 --> 00:09:45,148
How deep does that awareness go?

186
00:09:45,218 --> 00:09:46,618
Pick up scraps of conversations?

187
00:09:46,686 --> 00:09:47,813
Do you have the vague sense

188
00:09:47,887 --> 00:09:49,932
that the hospital administrator
dresses like a trollop?

189
00:09:49,956 --> 00:09:53,449
Or that the new <i>Star Wars</i>
movies were a disappointment?

190
00:09:56,029 --> 00:09:58,555
I know my wife is dead.

191
00:10:02,902 --> 00:10:04,928
I don't know how long it's been.

192
00:10:08,741 --> 00:10:10,141
Ten years.

193
00:10:15,348 --> 00:10:17,544
What's the last
thing you remember?

194
00:10:18,718 --> 00:10:20,186
The fire.

195
00:10:21,488 --> 00:10:24,048
My wife was in the bedroom,
she had taken a sleeping pill.

196
00:10:24,124 --> 00:10:28,027
I got Kyle out,
went back in for her.

197
00:10:29,896 --> 00:10:31,922
I knew I didn't make it.

198
00:10:31,998 --> 00:10:33,364
I'm sorry.

199
00:10:33,900 --> 00:10:37,200
What about your wife's side of the
family? Any history of seizures there?

200
00:10:37,270 --> 00:10:40,035
Your son Kyle is a patient here.

201
00:10:40,507 --> 00:10:44,137
I'm afraid his condition is
serious. He may be dying.

202
00:10:47,747 --> 00:10:51,115
No seizure issues on
my wife's side, either.

203
00:10:51,851 --> 00:10:54,878
What about that steak?
Nobody ever answered me.

204
00:10:59,893 --> 00:11:04,228
Rumor in the cafeteria was Caustic
Guy was waking up Coma Guy.

205
00:11:04,297 --> 00:11:05,993
Technically,
Vegetative State Guy

206
00:11:06,065 --> 00:11:08,398
was woken by, yeah, Caustic Guy.

207
00:11:08,468 --> 00:11:09,527
So what happened?

208
00:11:09,602 --> 00:11:12,766
I gotta get him a steak before I
can ask him any more questions.

209
00:11:12,839 --> 00:11:14,273
He doesn't wanna
talk about his son?

210
00:11:14,340 --> 00:11:17,242
Didn't seem to emotionally
register that his son is sick.

211
00:11:17,310 --> 00:11:18,369
Brain issue?

212
00:11:18,444 --> 00:11:21,107
He was asphyxiated, spent
10 years as asparagus,

213
00:11:21,181 --> 00:11:23,343
who knows what damage
is in there. It's possible.

214
00:11:23,416 --> 00:11:25,647
Of course there's always
the simple explanation.

215
00:11:25,718 --> 00:11:27,880
Maybe he just
doesn't like his son.

216
00:11:28,188 --> 00:11:30,054
Only in your world
would that be simple.

217
00:11:30,123 --> 00:11:32,183
The delusion that
fathering a child

218
00:11:32,258 --> 00:11:34,591
installs a permanent
geyser of unconditional love...

219
00:11:34,661 --> 00:11:37,256
Maybe your father's feelings
were conditional, not everyone's.

220
00:11:37,330 --> 00:11:38,440
Well, of course,
that would play into

221
00:11:38,464 --> 00:11:39,864
your romantic vision of human...

222
00:11:39,933 --> 00:11:41,333
In terms you would understand,

223
00:11:41,401 --> 00:11:42,994
we have an
evolutionary incentive

224
00:11:43,069 --> 00:11:44,537
to sacrifice for our offspring.

225
00:11:44,604 --> 00:11:47,699
Our tribe, our friends.
Keep them safe.

226
00:11:49,042 --> 00:11:51,238
Except for all the
people who don't.

227
00:11:51,678 --> 00:11:53,408
Everything is conditional.

228
00:11:54,280 --> 00:11:57,375
You just can't always
anticipate the conditions.

229
00:12:07,327 --> 00:12:09,455
Mind if we talk
for a few minutes?

230
00:12:10,930 --> 00:12:14,389
How many pills would you
say Dr. House takes a day?

231
00:12:15,635 --> 00:12:17,627
I'm uncomfortable
setting a number.

232
00:12:17,704 --> 00:12:19,195
Well, try.

233
00:12:20,373 --> 00:12:21,602
Six.

234
00:12:22,976 --> 00:12:24,171
A day?

235
00:12:26,145 --> 00:12:29,582
Has he ever had you
write prescriptions for him?

236
00:12:30,283 --> 00:12:32,411
No. What is it you
want me to say?

237
00:12:32,485 --> 00:12:34,830
That he takes too many pills
and is a danger to the hospital,

238
00:12:34,854 --> 00:12:38,222
or he takes too few because
he's selling them on the side?

239
00:12:38,291 --> 00:12:40,021
Either one is ridiculous.

240
00:12:40,560 --> 00:12:42,188
I meant the former.

241
00:12:42,262 --> 00:12:43,730
You're wrong.

242
00:12:43,863 --> 00:12:47,857
Can I ask what Dr. House has
done to deserve your loyalty?

243
00:12:48,401 --> 00:12:49,994
He's not known as a great boss.

244
00:12:50,069 --> 00:12:51,594
He's not even much of a friend.

245
00:12:51,671 --> 00:12:54,732
Look how he left
Dr. Wilson holding the bag.

246
00:12:58,678 --> 00:13:01,910
It's odd. You don't
know about that?

247
00:13:02,448 --> 00:13:07,250
You defend him, and he won't even
tell you what's happening in his life.

248
00:13:19,198 --> 00:13:20,666
I was paged.

249
00:13:20,733 --> 00:13:21,792
We saw you with the cop.

250
00:13:21,868 --> 00:13:23,029
What'd he want?

251
00:13:23,102 --> 00:13:24,536
How many pills does House take,

252
00:13:24,604 --> 00:13:25,948
did I ever write
him a prescription?

253
00:13:25,972 --> 00:13:27,440
That sort of stuff.

254
00:13:28,274 --> 00:13:30,573
I told him six. A
day or in a mouthful?

255
00:13:30,643 --> 00:13:32,655
I was just hoping you guys
would stay consistent with...

256
00:13:32,679 --> 00:13:34,307
He wants to talk to us, too?

257
00:13:34,380 --> 00:13:35,780
You're next.

258
00:13:37,550 --> 00:13:39,280
We've gotta tell
House what's going on.

259
00:13:39,352 --> 00:13:41,218
Tritter says no. Then no it is.

260
00:13:41,287 --> 00:13:44,451
Cops have a thousand ways
to make life difficult for you.

261
00:13:44,624 --> 00:13:46,786
Quick. What's the kid's status?

262
00:13:46,859 --> 00:13:48,099
I gotta get back to our sleeper

263
00:13:48,127 --> 00:13:50,926
before he goes looking
for the orgasmatron.

264
00:13:53,599 --> 00:13:55,500
See, if that were rhetorical,

265
00:13:55,568 --> 00:13:57,613
it would mean that I can just
turn around and leave now,

266
00:13:57,637 --> 00:13:59,415
which I'm not doing, from
which you should deduce...

267
00:13:59,439 --> 00:14:01,772
He's off all drugs
except the antibiotics.

268
00:14:01,841 --> 00:14:03,776
His liver's just managing
to hang in there.

269
00:14:03,843 --> 00:14:06,039
He's still sliding into coma.

270
00:14:18,591 --> 00:14:20,253
Your barber sucks.

271
00:14:21,260 --> 00:14:24,594
Hey, Coma Diet,

272
00:14:24,664 --> 00:14:26,064
I could make a fortune.

273
00:14:26,132 --> 00:14:27,930
Vegetative State Diet.

274
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:29,332
Who gave you your clothes?

275
00:14:29,402 --> 00:14:30,734
Dr. Cuddy.

276
00:14:30,903 --> 00:14:32,997
I guess I'll need all
new ones, anyway.

277
00:14:33,072 --> 00:14:34,631
Everything went in the fire.

278
00:14:34,707 --> 00:14:35,834
Don't worry about it.

279
00:14:35,908 --> 00:14:39,310
We use recyclable clothes now.
Wear them once, then eat them.

280
00:14:40,179 --> 00:14:42,307
Your son's measles vaccination,

281
00:14:42,382 --> 00:14:44,126
do you remember if he
had it, what type it was?

282
00:14:44,150 --> 00:14:46,676
Man, you're a piece
of work, you know that?

283
00:14:48,321 --> 00:14:50,313
You weren't gonna
tell me, were you?

284
00:14:50,390 --> 00:14:51,390
I don't need new clothes.

285
00:14:51,457 --> 00:14:54,291
Dr. Cuddy says my body
will adjust to the drugs,

286
00:14:54,360 --> 00:14:56,352
that I'll be a vegetable
again by tomorrow.

287
00:14:56,429 --> 00:14:58,989
If I'm really lucky,
the day after.

288
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:01,400
Yeah.

289
00:15:01,934 --> 00:15:02,974
If I've got a day to live,

290
00:15:03,002 --> 00:15:05,301
I'm not gonna spend it in a
hospital room being grilled.

291
00:15:05,371 --> 00:15:07,101
Come on, where you gonna go?

292
00:15:07,173 --> 00:15:10,940
Your house burned down, your
wife's dead. Business was sold off.

293
00:15:11,010 --> 00:15:15,141
The only thing you have left is down
the hall, heading for a liver biopsy.

294
00:15:16,716 --> 00:15:22,280
Used to be this little hole in the
wall run by a guy named Giancarlo.

295
00:15:23,356 --> 00:15:25,325
Made the best
hoagies in the world.

296
00:15:25,391 --> 00:15:28,657
Real Italian rolls,
prosciutto, provolone...

297
00:15:31,531 --> 00:15:33,659
How far is Atlantic
City from here?

298
00:15:33,733 --> 00:15:37,226
You have one day to live,
and you want a sandwich?

299
00:15:37,303 --> 00:15:39,295
People on death
row get a last meal.

300
00:15:39,372 --> 00:15:42,570
The state provides it.
Who's providing for you?

301
00:15:44,076 --> 00:15:45,772
You got a car? Money?

302
00:15:47,313 --> 00:15:49,475
You're negotiating with me.

303
00:15:55,221 --> 00:15:58,851
Take out another 100 for
me. And I need your car.

304
00:15:58,925 --> 00:16:00,655
I'm not doing you any favors.

305
00:16:00,726 --> 00:16:03,321
You'll get it back
tomorrow. Two days, max.

306
00:16:03,830 --> 00:16:05,196
Road trip.

307
00:16:12,138 --> 00:16:14,198
This is like trying to
control the weather,

308
00:16:14,273 --> 00:16:16,401
but I'd prefer it if you
didn't eat in the car,

309
00:16:16,476 --> 00:16:17,910
I just had it detailed.

310
00:16:17,977 --> 00:16:19,741
I drive. Oh, the hell he does.

311
00:16:19,812 --> 00:16:20,939
Sure.

312
00:16:21,881 --> 00:16:24,783
Aside from the fact he just
woke up from a vegetative state,

313
00:16:24,851 --> 00:16:25,994
the guy doesn't have a license.

314
00:16:26,018 --> 00:16:28,817
How about this?
Cops stop us, we lie.

315
00:16:28,888 --> 00:16:31,289
You know how to do that. Chips.

316
00:16:34,494 --> 00:16:36,205
It's all the drugs pumping
through his system.

317
00:16:36,229 --> 00:16:38,926
Right now his reflexes are
better than Dale Earnhardt Jr's.

318
00:16:38,998 --> 00:16:41,558
What's this? It says ipod.

319
00:16:44,770 --> 00:16:46,238
I'm coming.

320
00:16:53,179 --> 00:16:55,876
So let's talk about
toxic exposure.

321
00:17:00,786 --> 00:17:04,245
What was wrong with the
old colors? I trusted brown.

322
00:17:05,024 --> 00:17:06,890
Do the purple ones
have chocolate inside?

323
00:17:06,959 --> 00:17:08,427
Raspberry cocaine.

324
00:17:09,095 --> 00:17:11,428
This house that burned
down, where was it?

325
00:17:11,497 --> 00:17:12,795
Moorestown, New Jersey.

326
00:17:12,865 --> 00:17:16,734
Listen, I really need to know about
the candy because I'm allergic to berries.

327
00:17:16,802 --> 00:17:17,802
You didn't mention that.

328
00:17:17,870 --> 00:17:19,202
Is it significant?

329
00:17:19,272 --> 00:17:21,673
No. So where else did you live?

330
00:17:21,741 --> 00:17:23,676
List everywhere,
including vacations,

331
00:17:23,743 --> 00:17:25,473
start with when your
wife got pregnant.

332
00:17:25,545 --> 00:17:29,073
We lived in Jersey. Then we
moved to Jersey, from there, Jersey.

333
00:17:29,148 --> 00:17:32,209
What are you waiting to hear?
About the little cottage in the Amazon

334
00:17:32,285 --> 00:17:34,566
with the mosquitoes and the
lead paint all over the walls?

335
00:17:34,620 --> 00:17:35,679
Yes.

336
00:17:36,455 --> 00:17:37,455
You know what?

337
00:17:37,523 --> 00:17:41,654
I didn't let you come along so you could
suck all the fun out of my one day of life.

338
00:17:41,727 --> 00:17:45,095
Well, you're outta luck, because
that's totally why I'm here.

339
00:17:47,033 --> 00:17:49,059
Okay, rule change.

340
00:17:50,336 --> 00:17:52,601
Person with the money
makes the rules. Or in this case,

341
00:17:52,672 --> 00:17:56,131
the person who's friends with the
person with the money makes the rules.

342
00:17:56,208 --> 00:17:58,837
Well, you want answers
more than I want money.

343
00:17:59,111 --> 00:18:01,046
All right, so here's the game.

344
00:18:01,414 --> 00:18:02,677
Ask whatever you want.

345
00:18:02,748 --> 00:18:06,310
But for every question I answer,
you have to answer one first.

346
00:18:06,385 --> 00:18:08,581
Why would you care about
anything I have to say?

347
00:18:08,654 --> 00:18:11,920
The day before I died,
I was a successful man.

348
00:18:12,558 --> 00:18:15,995
I had a factory with
over 200 employees.

349
00:18:16,062 --> 00:18:17,997
People listened when I talked.

350
00:18:18,397 --> 00:18:20,298
I liked power.

351
00:18:22,034 --> 00:18:26,870
Now, the only power I have
left is the power to annoy you.

352
00:18:33,879 --> 00:18:36,075
I took Wilson's
assistant for coffee.

353
00:18:36,148 --> 00:18:38,617
Why? Something Tritter said.

354
00:18:38,684 --> 00:18:39,982
She told me the police think

355
00:18:40,052 --> 00:18:43,784
that House stole Wilson's
prescription pad and forged his name.

356
00:18:44,957 --> 00:18:46,482
You believe it?

357
00:18:47,927 --> 00:18:49,725
Do you? Well, absolutely I do.

358
00:18:49,795 --> 00:18:51,388
I'm just checking
how naive you are.

359
00:18:51,464 --> 00:18:54,093
He's not gonna steal his best
friend's pad, jeopardize his career.

360
00:18:54,166 --> 00:18:56,192
Until his best friend
says no to him.

361
00:18:56,268 --> 00:18:57,497
House is a junkie.

362
00:18:57,570 --> 00:19:00,802
Junkies do whatever they
have to do to get what they need.

363
00:19:02,942 --> 00:19:05,537
Kyle's down to a three
on the RLAS scale.

364
00:19:06,112 --> 00:19:08,377
He's only showing
localized response.

365
00:19:08,748 --> 00:19:11,980
I'll call House, tell him we're
gonna need an answer soon.

366
00:19:14,453 --> 00:19:16,718
Get in your right lane for 295.

367
00:19:17,423 --> 00:19:19,153
And pass me the Twizzlers.

368
00:19:23,262 --> 00:19:25,026
I'm curious... No, you're not.

369
00:19:25,097 --> 00:19:26,690
Why would a man's first instinct

370
00:19:26,766 --> 00:19:28,826
be to drive away from
the only family he's got?

371
00:19:28,901 --> 00:19:31,871
No, this is no time for
you to do your thing.

372
00:19:31,937 --> 00:19:34,549
We don't care about his state of
mind, we don't care if he's happy.

373
00:19:34,573 --> 00:19:37,042
This factory of yours,
what did you make?

374
00:19:41,047 --> 00:19:42,811
So ask me a question.

375
00:19:43,282 --> 00:19:44,341
I'm thinking.

376
00:19:44,417 --> 00:19:46,181
Only six left, by the way.

377
00:19:46,252 --> 00:19:48,881
So sign my name. You don't
need a doctor, you need a pen.

378
00:19:48,954 --> 00:19:50,252
What is up with you two?

379
00:19:50,322 --> 00:19:53,656
Wilson lied to the bulls to
keep me out of the big house.

380
00:19:53,726 --> 00:19:54,955
Are you out of your mind?

381
00:19:55,027 --> 00:19:56,655
Well, who's he gonna tell?

382
00:19:56,729 --> 00:19:59,995
By tomorrow night he's gonna
be a mindless stalk of celery.

383
00:20:00,132 --> 00:20:03,068
Since I answered that
one, by the way, my turn.

384
00:20:03,135 --> 00:20:04,501
What did you make
in your factory?

385
00:20:04,570 --> 00:20:06,004
Luxury boats.

386
00:20:07,139 --> 00:20:08,539
Have you ever been in love?

387
00:20:08,607 --> 00:20:09,700
Wow!

388
00:20:09,775 --> 00:20:12,506
Going right for the closets with
the embarrassing stuff. Good move.

389
00:20:12,578 --> 00:20:14,570
Yes. Describe the boats.

390
00:20:14,647 --> 00:20:18,482
Thirty-five to 65-foot hulls, twin
engines, parquet floors in the galley,

391
00:20:18,551 --> 00:20:20,645
staterooms with queen beds.

392
00:20:21,520 --> 00:20:23,682
How'd you meet? She shot me.

393
00:20:24,156 --> 00:20:27,649
These boats, I assume you used
mildew-resistant paint on the hulls?

394
00:20:27,727 --> 00:20:29,355
Naturally. Shot you?

395
00:20:29,929 --> 00:20:33,229
Paintball. Doctors
versus lawyers.

396
00:20:33,299 --> 00:20:35,393
Did you ever take your
son to the factory? Sure.

397
00:20:35,468 --> 00:20:38,836
He used to run all over the
place, but it was perfectly safe.

398
00:20:39,872 --> 00:20:41,500
Ever love anybody else?

399
00:20:42,341 --> 00:20:45,175
No more questions,
I got my answer.

400
00:20:45,244 --> 00:20:48,908
While Dad's in the office, his
son's watching them spray-paint.

401
00:20:48,981 --> 00:20:50,847
And what kid wears a mask?

402
00:20:50,916 --> 00:20:53,647
Mercury specifically targets
the central nervous system.

403
00:20:53,719 --> 00:20:54,930
You're saying this is my fault?

404
00:20:54,954 --> 00:20:57,219
Mercury poisoning
explains the seizures

405
00:20:57,289 --> 00:20:59,224
and the liver's like
a big soup strainer.

406
00:20:59,291 --> 00:21:01,760
The soup runs through,
chicken dumplings stay.

407
00:21:01,827 --> 00:21:03,523
For soup, read
blood, for chicken...

408
00:21:03,596 --> 00:21:05,087
I get it, I get it. Mercury.

409
00:21:05,164 --> 00:21:06,359
Sits more or less idle

410
00:21:06,432 --> 00:21:09,732
until your kid pours tequila
shooters into his liver.

411
00:21:10,269 --> 00:21:13,569
When the liver goes, takes out
the kidneys, explains everything.

412
00:21:13,639 --> 00:21:14,663
Yeah, it's me.

413
00:21:14,740 --> 00:21:17,676
<i>Foreman, draw blood.
Test for mercury poisoning.</i>

414
00:21:17,743 --> 00:21:19,735
Chase, start heavy
metal chelation

415
00:21:19,812 --> 00:21:21,610
while we're waiting for results.

416
00:21:22,248 --> 00:21:24,114
Chase isn't here.
I'll start the...

417
00:21:24,183 --> 00:21:25,344
Where is he?

418
00:21:27,353 --> 00:21:28,353
The lab.

419
00:21:32,892 --> 00:21:35,327
How many pills
does he take a day?

420
00:21:35,861 --> 00:21:39,229
It's hard to say, pain
levels vary over time...

421
00:21:39,298 --> 00:21:42,393
Could be six, eight, 10.

422
00:21:42,835 --> 00:21:44,736
Ever write any
prescriptions for him?

423
00:21:44,804 --> 00:21:46,363
Yes. Why?

424
00:21:46,438 --> 00:21:48,134
Did he tell you to?

425
00:21:48,607 --> 00:21:50,166
He asked me to.

426
00:21:57,249 --> 00:22:02,950
Medicine attracts people
who are attracted to power.

427
00:22:03,622 --> 00:22:07,787
I know how he hates when
he is defied by a patient.

428
00:22:08,861 --> 00:22:12,423
I doubt he handles defiance
from his staff any better.

429
00:22:12,498 --> 00:22:14,490
Now you correct me if I'm wrong,

430
00:22:14,567 --> 00:22:18,197
but I don't think Dr. House
asks for anything.

431
00:22:19,138 --> 00:22:21,164
I think he takes it.

432
00:22:21,240 --> 00:22:26,201
And I think that you are
stuck lying to the police

433
00:22:27,179 --> 00:22:30,911
to cover up something
you didn't wanna do.

434
00:22:39,258 --> 00:22:42,319
We have been up and down
St. James like a Monopoly car.

435
00:22:42,394 --> 00:22:45,592
It's not here. Giancarlo
has left the building.

436
00:22:50,035 --> 00:22:51,847
We can still turn around
and go back to Princeton.

437
00:22:51,871 --> 00:22:54,602
No. We've come this
far, I'm getting the hoagie.

438
00:22:57,743 --> 00:22:59,871
If your son does have
mercury poisoning,

439
00:22:59,945 --> 00:23:01,790
there's a good chance he'll
respond to the chelation.

440
00:23:01,814 --> 00:23:04,226
You might be able to have a few
minutes with him before you lapse.

441
00:23:04,250 --> 00:23:06,549
Why are you so
concerned about me?

442
00:23:07,753 --> 00:23:10,587
Deep inside Wilson believes
that if he cares enough

443
00:23:10,656 --> 00:23:12,352
he'll never have to die.

444
00:23:12,925 --> 00:23:15,053
Your behavior isn't normal.

445
00:23:15,394 --> 00:23:16,953
And you would know normal?

446
00:23:17,029 --> 00:23:20,261
What could he have done that
you won't forgive after 10 years?

447
00:23:20,332 --> 00:23:22,392
When this is your last chance?

448
00:23:23,535 --> 00:23:25,766
My son is what he is.

449
00:23:25,838 --> 00:23:28,637
His mother's side,
all drunken losers.

450
00:23:30,009 --> 00:23:31,773
He's gone the same way.

451
00:23:32,711 --> 00:23:36,113
House told you drinking
had damaged your son's liver.

452
00:23:36,181 --> 00:23:37,376
I just said that.

453
00:23:37,449 --> 00:23:38,849
But you didn't hear him say that

454
00:23:38,918 --> 00:23:40,819
until after we
left the hospital.

455
00:23:40,886 --> 00:23:42,718
So why did you leave?

456
00:23:44,623 --> 00:23:47,092
Maybe your son
takes after your side.

457
00:23:47,927 --> 00:23:50,453
Seizures and an allergy
to emotional connections.

458
00:23:50,529 --> 00:23:52,327
Okay, okay, okay. Enough.

459
00:23:53,432 --> 00:23:56,402
We're in Atlantic City
and my time's not up yet.

460
00:23:56,468 --> 00:23:58,994
We find a hotel with a casino.

461
00:24:05,010 --> 00:24:06,569
BP's starting to drop.

462
00:24:07,179 --> 00:24:08,875
O2-sat's down to 70.

463
00:24:13,352 --> 00:24:15,184
Point-three
milligrams of epi in.

464
00:24:15,254 --> 00:24:17,032
What are you trying to
do, make him bleed faster?

465
00:24:17,056 --> 00:24:18,752
Check the pulse.

466
00:24:19,525 --> 00:24:21,187
It's not his liver.

467
00:24:22,294 --> 00:24:23,887
It's the heart.

468
00:24:25,130 --> 00:24:26,689
I understand he's a French chef

469
00:24:26,765 --> 00:24:28,666
but I'm sure he can handle this.

470
00:24:28,734 --> 00:24:30,703
You need a 12-inch Italian roll,

471
00:24:30,769 --> 00:24:35,002
oregano vinegar, no, not
balsamic vinegar, oregano vinegar.

472
00:24:35,841 --> 00:24:38,174
Quid pro quo, Clarice.

473
00:24:38,677 --> 00:24:40,009
Game's still on.

474
00:24:40,079 --> 00:24:42,378
I thought the answer
was mercury poisoning.

475
00:24:42,448 --> 00:24:44,440
What other questions
would you care about?

476
00:24:44,516 --> 00:24:45,694
If you each had one day to live,

477
00:24:45,718 --> 00:24:49,519
you'd look for one last meal and
House would look for one last answer.

478
00:24:50,489 --> 00:24:52,685
No, can you just send
the ingredients up here

479
00:24:52,758 --> 00:24:54,784
and I'll make it myself.

480
00:24:55,594 --> 00:24:59,292
Last 10 years, how much
awareness did you have?

481
00:24:59,365 --> 00:25:02,267
I don't know, I knew
it wasn't the next day.

482
00:25:02,334 --> 00:25:03,802
I knew that...

483
00:25:04,970 --> 00:25:06,666
I recognized your voice.

484
00:25:07,639 --> 00:25:09,471
How often were you in my room?

485
00:25:09,541 --> 00:25:11,772
No, you're wasting a question.

486
00:25:11,844 --> 00:25:13,312
I have a better one.

487
00:25:14,980 --> 00:25:16,608
Why steal my pad?

488
00:25:16,682 --> 00:25:19,481
Oh, my God, you're
right. I'm an addict.

489
00:25:19,551 --> 00:25:21,110
Thanks for opening my eyes.

490
00:25:21,186 --> 00:25:23,052
No, I mean why my pad?

491
00:25:23,288 --> 00:25:26,452
Foreman, Cameron and Chase's
pads are just as convenient.

492
00:25:26,525 --> 00:25:29,461
But their association with you is
involuntary, they're employees.

493
00:25:29,528 --> 00:25:31,429
I associate with
you through choice

494
00:25:31,497 --> 00:25:33,193
and any relationship
that involves choice

495
00:25:33,265 --> 00:25:35,928
you have to see how far
you can push before it breaks.

496
00:25:36,001 --> 00:25:37,367
This is easy.

497
00:25:37,436 --> 00:25:40,964
You ask the questions, answer
them and make tasty snacks.

498
00:25:41,573 --> 00:25:43,599
Let's go try the casino.

499
00:25:43,675 --> 00:25:45,576
And one day our
friendship will break

500
00:25:45,644 --> 00:25:49,103
and that'll just prove your theory
that relationships are conditional

501
00:25:49,181 --> 00:25:51,844
and you don't need human
connection or deserve it,

502
00:25:51,917 --> 00:25:55,115
or whatever goes on in
that rat-maze of your brain.

503
00:25:55,254 --> 00:25:57,348
Sorry, if I'd known he was
gonna be this annoying,

504
00:25:57,423 --> 00:25:59,085
I would have stolen
Dr. Cameron's pad

505
00:25:59,158 --> 00:26:00,902
and Dr. Foreman's car.

506
00:26:00,926 --> 00:26:04,021
At least she appreciates
my brooding melancholy.

507
00:26:04,496 --> 00:26:07,261
House's House of Whining,
state your complaint.

508
00:26:07,332 --> 00:26:08,977
The patient's BP just
dropped like a stone.

509
00:26:09,001 --> 00:26:10,025
<i>Do an echo.</i>

510
00:26:10,102 --> 00:26:11,542
Mercury isn't likely
to damage the...

511
00:26:11,603 --> 00:26:12,662
<i>It didn't.</i>

512
00:26:12,738 --> 00:26:14,764
Mercury test was negative.

513
00:26:16,508 --> 00:26:17,942
Do an echo.

514
00:26:24,316 --> 00:26:27,286
I was wrong. Your
son's still dying.

515
00:26:27,920 --> 00:26:30,856
I need to go over every
relative you ever had. Again.

516
00:26:30,923 --> 00:26:34,189
And this time, forget their
diseases, just tell me how they died.

517
00:26:34,259 --> 00:26:36,251
And we don't have
time to take turns.

518
00:26:36,328 --> 00:26:38,559
You give me the answers,
you get a big one at the end.

519
00:26:38,630 --> 00:26:40,098
