whatever you want.

520
00:26:40,165 --> 00:26:42,634
Destroy my privacy, my dignity.

521
00:26:49,908 --> 00:26:51,376
Your grandmother?

522
00:26:51,443 --> 00:26:53,605
Heat exhaustion,
Fourth of July picnic.

523
00:26:53,679 --> 00:26:55,170
The woman was 92.

524
00:26:55,247 --> 00:26:57,580
Does anyone in the kitchen
know the hoagie shop

525
00:26:57,649 --> 00:26:59,413
that used to be on
St. James Place?

526
00:26:59,485 --> 00:27:01,750
You sister-in-law
with the diabetes.

527
00:27:01,820 --> 00:27:03,731
As far as you know, is
she still alive? She's not.

528
00:27:03,755 --> 00:27:04,966
She was killed in
a traffic accident

529
00:27:04,990 --> 00:27:06,583
driving home from
a Phillies game.

530
00:27:06,658 --> 00:27:08,251
I'm sure a lot of
beer was consumed.

531
00:27:08,327 --> 00:27:10,193
The Phillies lost. Your father?

532
00:27:10,262 --> 00:27:12,458
Old age. Heart finally gave out.

533
00:27:12,865 --> 00:27:13,865
Your wife's father?

534
00:27:13,932 --> 00:27:16,595
Hit-and-run, walking
the incontinent dog.

535
00:27:17,402 --> 00:27:19,394
Hi, do you guys deliver?

536
00:27:20,973 --> 00:27:21,997
Let me put it this way,

537
00:27:22,074 --> 00:27:25,135
if you deliver, there'll
be a $100 tip in it for you.

538
00:27:26,145 --> 00:27:27,374
Excellent.

539
00:27:27,980 --> 00:27:31,007
Victory. The night is
finally going my way.

540
00:27:31,416 --> 00:27:33,317
Wilson, toss me a soda.

541
00:27:48,033 --> 00:27:50,093
Shall we go somewhere to talk?

542
00:27:50,936 --> 00:27:52,302
House is an ass.

543
00:27:52,371 --> 00:27:54,499
But he obviously
needs pain medication,

544
00:27:54,573 --> 00:27:55,973
and how much pain
one person feels

545
00:27:56,041 --> 00:27:58,510
is not a call the government
should be making.

546
00:27:58,577 --> 00:28:00,671
So you think I'm a
bureaucrat with a badge

547
00:28:00,746 --> 00:28:02,942
following some
arbitrary guideline.

548
00:28:03,582 --> 00:28:04,845
Yeah, I do.

549
00:28:05,551 --> 00:28:09,750
So you're saying I should
just trust him. Do you?

550
00:28:09,821 --> 00:28:11,289
You're not qualified
to make that...

551
00:28:11,356 --> 00:28:13,291
I'm not sure you are, either.

552
00:28:13,358 --> 00:28:15,327
I've been a cop for 20 years.

553
00:28:15,394 --> 00:28:16,453
And not a day goes by

554
00:28:16,528 --> 00:28:20,989
that someone doesn't try to
sell me some self-serving story.

555
00:28:21,800 --> 00:28:23,735
If you had my job, you'd know.

556
00:28:25,204 --> 00:28:26,832
Everybody lies.

557
00:28:34,012 --> 00:28:36,208
I think you've run
out of relatives.

558
00:28:36,915 --> 00:28:38,611
So, it's my turn.

559
00:28:43,755 --> 00:28:45,621
Why did you become a doctor?

560
00:28:45,691 --> 00:28:47,091
That's the big question?

561
00:28:47,893 --> 00:28:49,862
I give you complete
license to humiliate me

562
00:28:49,928 --> 00:28:51,294
and that's the best you can do.

563
00:28:51,363 --> 00:28:54,492
Well, okay, let's discuss the
wonder of the human body.

564
00:28:54,566 --> 00:28:56,762
No, no, no. You're
a curious guy.

565
00:28:57,502 --> 00:29:00,233
You like to figure things
out, why not go into research?

566
00:29:00,305 --> 00:29:01,933
Why work with people when you

567
00:29:02,941 --> 00:29:04,432
obviously hate people?

568
00:29:06,044 --> 00:29:07,569
Oedipal fixation.

569
00:29:07,646 --> 00:29:09,046
I was seeking my mother's love

570
00:29:09,114 --> 00:29:11,259
and she thought that Ben
Casey was just the dreamiest...

571
00:29:11,283 --> 00:29:14,845
Okay, fine. You don't think you'll
need any more answers from me?

572
00:29:15,120 --> 00:29:16,782
Give me a hard time.

573
00:29:26,131 --> 00:29:27,622
When I was 14,

574
00:29:29,001 --> 00:29:31,334
my father was
stationed in Japan.

575
00:29:32,137 --> 00:29:34,732
I went rock-climbing
with this kid from school.

576
00:29:34,806 --> 00:29:38,334
He fell and got injured and I
had to bring him to the hospital.

577
00:29:39,878 --> 00:29:41,938
And we came in through
the wrong entrance

578
00:29:42,014 --> 00:29:44,040
and passed this guy in the hall.

579
00:29:45,584 --> 00:29:47,018
He was a janitor.

580
00:29:47,352 --> 00:29:49,344
My friend came
down with an infection

581
00:29:49,421 --> 00:29:51,617
and the doctors
didn't know what to do.

582
00:29:52,624 --> 00:29:54,024
So they brought in

583
00:29:55,661 --> 00:29:57,095
the janitor.

584
00:29:59,798 --> 00:30:01,426
He was a doctor.

585
00:30:02,934 --> 00:30:04,903
And a <i>buraku.</i>

586
00:30:06,271 --> 00:30:08,502
One of Japan's untouchables.

587
00:30:09,775 --> 00:30:13,610
His ancestors had been
slaughterers, gravediggers.

588
00:30:14,913 --> 00:30:16,142
And this guy,

589
00:30:17,949 --> 00:30:20,612
he knew that he wasn't accepted
by the staff, didn't even try.

590
00:30:20,686 --> 00:30:23,918
He didn't dress well, he didn't
pretend to be one of them.

591
00:30:25,457 --> 00:30:27,255
The people around that place,

592
00:30:27,326 --> 00:30:29,955
they didn't think he had
anything they wanted,

593
00:30:32,264 --> 00:30:34,096
except when they needed him.

594
00:30:35,534 --> 00:30:37,298
Because he was right.

595
00:30:39,338 --> 00:30:41,705
Which meant that
nothing else mattered.

596
00:30:42,841 --> 00:30:45,072
And they had to listen to him.

597
00:30:54,419 --> 00:30:55,512
Thank you.

598
00:30:59,491 --> 00:31:02,017
Need 20 milligrams of
diazepam in a syringe.

599
00:31:10,068 --> 00:31:12,037
Heartbeat's irregular
and accelerating.

600
00:31:12,104 --> 00:31:13,629
He's at 200. He's gonna crash.

601
00:31:13,705 --> 00:31:14,949
Allergic reaction
to the diazepam?

602
00:31:14,973 --> 00:31:15,997
Better hope so.

603
00:31:16,074 --> 00:31:18,737
It's either that or
his heart's done.

604
00:31:26,251 --> 00:31:28,686
What happened on
the night of the fire?

605
00:31:32,457 --> 00:31:35,950
Yeah. I'm sure it's a
stressful, emotional question.

606
00:31:36,027 --> 00:31:37,188
Suck it up.

607
00:31:40,465 --> 00:31:43,128
My wife had taken a
sleeping pill and gone to bed.

608
00:31:43,201 --> 00:31:44,225
It was Christmas Eve.

609
00:31:44,302 --> 00:31:47,238
I let Kyle pop corn
in the fireplace.

610
00:31:48,240 --> 00:31:51,369
He managed to knock
loose some tinder.

611
00:31:52,244 --> 00:31:53,872
Wrapping paper caught on fire.

612
00:31:53,945 --> 00:31:56,141
It spread so fast.

613
00:31:56,314 --> 00:31:58,044
I got Kyle out and...

614
00:31:59,084 --> 00:32:00,814
When I went back in for...

615
00:32:05,357 --> 00:32:07,053
You're a disappointment.

616
00:32:08,627 --> 00:32:12,086
You act as though you
don't need anybody, you...

617
00:32:12,164 --> 00:32:14,258
You just blame your
son for what happened.

618
00:32:14,332 --> 00:32:17,200
I don't blame him. He
was a 12-year-old boy.

619
00:32:17,269 --> 00:32:19,204
You don't blame a
kid for an accident.

620
00:32:19,271 --> 00:32:21,182
Then what are we doing
here? Why aren't you with him?

621
00:32:21,206 --> 00:32:23,004
Because it wouldn't matter.

622
00:32:23,074 --> 00:32:25,976
I failed to keep my family safe.

623
00:32:26,044 --> 00:32:29,879
I couldn't stop the fire,
I couldn't save my wife,

624
00:32:29,948 --> 00:32:33,680
now you want me to stick around
watching while I fail to save my son.

625
00:32:33,752 --> 00:32:36,221
Thank you so much
for waking me up.

626
00:32:43,328 --> 00:32:45,661
How did your son
dislodge the tinder?

627
00:32:46,731 --> 00:32:47,892
God...

628
00:32:51,303 --> 00:32:53,272
He dropped the popcorn tray.

629
00:32:53,338 --> 00:32:56,536
He had been complaining it was
too heavy, I should have listened.

630
00:32:56,608 --> 00:33:00,067
And the hit-and-run,
walking the pissy dog.

631
00:33:00,145 --> 00:33:01,613
That happen at night?

632
00:33:01,680 --> 00:33:03,444
I think so, yeah, why?

633
00:33:03,515 --> 00:33:05,950
Car accident after
the Phillies lost.

634
00:33:06,017 --> 00:33:07,417
Night game?

635
00:33:09,855 --> 00:33:11,619
Ragged-red fiber.

636
00:33:11,690 --> 00:33:13,249
It's an inherited condition.

637
00:33:13,325 --> 00:33:16,420
Dropping things, muscle
weakness, poor night vision.

638
00:33:16,495 --> 00:33:20,262
Makes people seem uncoordinated,
accident-prone, careless.

639
00:33:20,332 --> 00:33:22,892
It's transmitted in
mitochondrial DNA

640
00:33:22,968 --> 00:33:24,869
so it only passes
through the mother.

641
00:33:24,936 --> 00:33:28,100
Your wife's family weren't
drunks, they were sick.

642
00:33:28,373 --> 00:33:30,274
It wouldn't have
affected his liver.

643
00:33:30,342 --> 00:33:31,810
The kid is a drunk.

644
00:33:31,877 --> 00:33:33,087
He thinks that he
killed his mother

645
00:33:33,111 --> 00:33:35,205
and turned his father
into a vegetable.

646
00:33:35,280 --> 00:33:37,442
I might have a few shots myself.

647
00:33:38,650 --> 00:33:39,743
<i>Foreman.</i>

648
00:33:39,818 --> 00:33:42,754
Test his DNA for
ragged-red fiber.

649
00:33:42,821 --> 00:33:44,517
It's not gonna...
<i>Here's a thought.</i>

650
00:33:44,589 --> 00:33:47,616
Why don't we not assume that the
test is negative until we actually do it?

651
00:33:47,692 --> 00:33:51,129
House, the kid has
severe cardiomyopathy.

652
00:33:52,030 --> 00:33:54,556
Alcoholic, no shot
at a transplant.

653
00:33:54,933 --> 00:33:58,097
So yeah, maybe you figured
out why, good for you, but

654
00:33:59,671 --> 00:34:01,537
he's gonna die anyway.

655
00:34:27,532 --> 00:34:29,763
I want to give Kyle my heart.

656
00:34:33,572 --> 00:34:38,374
This thing, whatever it is, you
said he gets it from the mother.

657
00:34:38,443 --> 00:34:39,604
My heart's fine.

658
00:34:39,678 --> 00:34:43,115
And it could go on being
fine for the rest of your life.

659
00:34:43,181 --> 00:34:46,208
Yeah, it's not like he's
gonna do anything with it.

660
00:34:46,284 --> 00:34:47,616
Well, you woke him up once,

661
00:34:47,686 --> 00:34:50,417
maybe someone'll come
up with some other answer.

662
00:34:50,589 --> 00:34:53,218
We've both seen
breakthroughs no one expected.

663
00:34:54,826 --> 00:34:57,990
And ragged-red fiber's
treatable, but not curable.

664
00:34:58,630 --> 00:35:01,429
Even if he gets your
heart, there's no guarantee.

665
00:35:03,868 --> 00:35:05,200
He's my kid.

666
00:35:06,905 --> 00:35:08,168
No!

667
00:35:08,239 --> 00:35:10,174
Did you really expect
a different answer?

668
00:35:10,241 --> 00:35:14,076
We have arranged transplants
before when a patient is near death.

669
00:35:14,145 --> 00:35:18,378
Except he isn't near death, he's
saying, "Kill me and cut out my heart."

670
00:35:18,450 --> 00:35:20,442
<i>Are you out of your mind?</i>

671
00:35:21,620 --> 00:35:24,021
Fine. I'll think of
something else.

672
00:35:25,757 --> 00:35:27,089
I'm sorry.

673
00:35:42,674 --> 00:35:45,701
Wilson, get out.

674
00:35:49,047 --> 00:35:50,106
No.

675
00:35:54,319 --> 00:35:56,515
You lied to the
cops enough for me.

676
00:36:00,759 --> 00:36:03,388
Maybe I don't wanna
push this till it breaks.

677
00:36:26,584 --> 00:36:28,917
Pills are the simplest.

678
00:36:32,624 --> 00:36:35,321
Hanging has less chance
of damaging the heart.

679
00:36:38,930 --> 00:36:40,626
I'm okay with pain.

680
00:36:42,467 --> 00:36:45,198
Strangulation is better
than breaking your neck,

681
00:36:46,771 --> 00:36:48,706
which means this'll be slow.

682
00:36:52,210 --> 00:36:55,647
I wouldn't get to see him even
if we got in the car right now

683
00:36:55,714 --> 00:36:58,775
and broke the speed
limit driving back, would I?

684
00:36:59,718 --> 00:37:00,947
No.

685
00:37:04,189 --> 00:37:05,418
Tell him...

686
00:37:14,532 --> 00:37:16,694
I don't know what to tell him.

687
00:37:23,842 --> 00:37:25,970
I think it's my turn to
ask a question, isn't it?

688
00:37:26,044 --> 00:37:27,410
I don't think so.

689
00:37:27,746 --> 00:37:30,978
'Cause you just asked me
that thing about the speed limit.

690
00:37:33,952 --> 00:37:35,614
What do you wanna know?

691
00:37:35,954 --> 00:37:39,652
If you could hear one thing
from your father, what would it be?

692
00:37:41,926 --> 00:37:43,394
It wouldn't help you.

693
00:37:43,461 --> 00:37:44,656
Try me.

694
00:37:49,968 --> 00:37:51,732
I'd want him to say,

695
00:37:55,173 --> 00:37:56,766
"You were right.

696
00:37:58,143 --> 00:38:00,078
"You did the right thing."

697
00:38:02,480 --> 00:38:05,416
Yeah. It doesn't help.

698
00:38:21,566 --> 00:38:23,262
Hi. Hi.

699
00:38:25,503 --> 00:38:27,028
I'm Dr. Wilson.

700
00:38:27,639 --> 00:38:29,301
I'm Mrs. Schaffer.

701
00:38:29,407 --> 00:38:31,103
I'm from Princeton.

702
00:38:32,310 --> 00:38:35,678
My husband and I and our
three children live in Philadelphia.

703
00:38:39,617 --> 00:38:43,418
So, do you like to swing?

704
00:38:45,890 --> 00:38:47,324
No.

705
00:38:47,992 --> 00:38:50,826
Well, if you change
your mind, I'm in...

706
00:38:53,231 --> 00:38:55,291
House? House?

707
00:38:55,366 --> 00:38:57,801
Is it room 622, 642?

708
00:38:58,236 --> 00:38:59,431
622.

709
00:39:00,171 --> 00:39:01,171
622.

710
00:39:01,806 --> 00:39:02,967
Yeah.

711
00:39:18,890 --> 00:39:20,085
Alibi.

712
00:39:22,594 --> 00:39:24,085
I figured.

713
00:40:11,509 --> 00:40:14,479
They found an open
bottle of aspirin by the body.

714
00:40:16,247 --> 00:40:20,514
Lucky he had a headache,
reduced trauma to the heart in transit.

715
00:40:22,153 --> 00:40:23,553
Lucky.

716
00:40:36,401 --> 00:40:38,063
That can't be all.

717
00:40:39,570 --> 00:40:41,562
Well, you got a heart out of it.

718
00:40:41,639 --> 00:40:43,699
How many organs do
you want from the guy?

719
00:40:43,775 --> 00:40:46,301
I mean, my father must
have said something.

720
00:40:47,145 --> 00:40:48,704
He couldn't just...

721
00:40:48,780 --> 00:40:51,944
He must have given you
some kind of a message for me.

722
00:40:58,156 --> 00:41:00,057
He said you were right.

723
00:41:00,491 --> 00:41:02,187
You did the right thing.

724
00:41:07,465 --> 00:41:09,229
Right about what?

725
00:41:11,169 --> 00:41:12,933
What does that mean?

726
00:41:13,972 --> 00:41:16,840
How would I know? He's your dad.

727
00:41:29,687 --> 00:41:32,521
You know what I found
interesting about this case?

728
00:41:32,924 --> 00:41:35,484
That it proved that people
can love unconditionally

729
00:41:35,560 --> 00:41:37,256
and you can tell
yourself it's not true,

730
00:41:37,328 --> 00:41:39,888
but you'll just end up in a
hotel room in Atlantic City

731
00:41:39,964 --> 00:41:41,557
asking someone to
cut your heart out?

732
00:41:41,632 --> 00:41:43,692
The hoagie.

733
00:41:43,768 --> 00:41:46,067
You thought this guy
was emotionally confused,

734
00:41:46,137 --> 00:41:47,833
and that the hoagie
was just a mask

735
00:41:47,905 --> 00:41:50,636
to hide his real
feelings toward his son.

736
00:41:50,742 --> 00:41:51,937
It was.

737
00:41:52,343 --> 00:41:55,040
Did you know Tritter was talking
to your team while we were away?

738
00:41:55,113 --> 00:41:56,113
Yeah.

739
00:41:56,681 --> 00:41:58,047
And yet you moved
Heaven and Earth

740
00:41:58,116 --> 00:42:01,109
to get him that mask with
mustard and prosciutto.

741
00:42:01,185 --> 00:42:02,744
Which one of them told you?

742
00:42:02,820 --> 00:42:03,844
All of them.

743
00:42:03,921 --> 00:42:06,550
Which means that none of them
said anything I have to worry about.

744
00:42:06,624 --> 00:42:08,002
Back to the hoagie.

745
00:42:08,026 --> 00:42:10,086
You think that my
addiction's out of hand.

746
00:42:10,161 --> 00:42:14,064
Your need to be needed is so strong
that you'll give people what they want,

747
00:42:14,132 --> 00:42:15,862
what they need, what
they think they need.

748
00:42:15,933 --> 00:42:19,734
I don't think my enabling is anything
you should be complaining about.

749
00:42:20,071 --> 00:42:22,370
Yes, my name is
